			<attribute id="HowToTrigger" type="LSString" value="" />
			<attribute id="needLayout" type="bool" value="False" />
			<attribute id="nextNodeId" type="uint32" value="17" />
			<attribute id="synopsis" type="LSString" value="This AD has two phases: the first plays if a druid ritual Elwyn was part of was stopped because their leader was exposed as a shadow druid. In this state, Elwyn is preoccupied with the goblins - she's afraid that without the protection the ritual would have provided, they don't have a chance against them.&#xD;&#xA;The second state plays once the goblins that threatened the grove - and necessitated the ritual - have been dealt with. In this state, Elwyn is calm, the weight of the goblin threat finally off her shoulders. " />
			<children>
				<node id="defaultAttitudes">
					<children>
						<node id="data">
